Using any of these requires you to understand whether you're writing a character or plot based story.
And one of the biggest flaws of modern film is they forget the basics of plot in exchange for the character journey. So you end up with woke "plots" which ignore reality harder than comic book movies handwave physics.

A better way of putting it is every action has a risk; whether it's readily apparent at that time or not. Or in fewer words, it's a trap!
